    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.62,
      696.25,
      527.18,
      709.29
    ],
    "text": "examining the witnesses, their credibility could be challenged. It could be achieved at the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.62,
      716.29,
      190.56,
      729.33
    ],
    "text": "Court of first instance.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      781.3,
      302.91,
      805.78
    ],
    "text": "4",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      75.27,
      526.21,
      104.77
    ],
    "text": "In the light of this contention, this Court will now determine whether it is, in fact, the appropriate forum to address this issue.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century",
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      126.29,
      488.62,
      139.77
    ],
    "text": "Wade and Forsyth in their text Administrative Law 11th Edition at p. 547 state,",
    "fonts": [
      "Century",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      6.960000038146973,
      11.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      71.31,
      162.29,
      529.84,
      175.33
    ],
    "text": "A feature of prerogative remedy procedure which remains unaltered in the modern",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      71.31,
      180.29,
      530.0,
      193.33
    ],
    "text": "procedure is that evidence is taken on affidavit i.e. by sworn statements in writing rather",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      71.31,
      198.29,
      530.11,
      211.33
    ],
    "text": "than orally. It is possible, but exceptional, for the court to allow cross-examination on the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      71.31,
      216.29,
      529.85,
      229.33
    ],
    "text": "affidavits. If the case turns upon a conflict of evidence, quashing and prohibiting orders",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      71.31,
      234.29,
      250.88,
      247.77
    ],
    "text": "may therefore involve difficulties.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      270.32,
      186.02,
      283.8
    ],
    "text": "And further at p. 557,",
    "fonts": [
      "Century",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      306.32,
      526.39,
      319.36
    ],
    "text": "Cross-examination was also only rarely allowed under Order 53. On the whole judicial",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      324.32,
      526.43,
      337.36
    ],
    "text": "review is not concerned with factual disputes and is ill-suited to resolve such disputes. In",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      342.32,
      523.5,
      355.36
    ],
    "text": "the absence of oral testimony courts rely on affidavit evidence without the benefit of cross-",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      360.32,
      526.27,
      373.36
    ],
    "text": "examination, and generally take the facts where they are in issue as they are deposed to",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      378.32,
      526.24,
      391.36
    ],
    "text": "by the public authority. But factual disputes can arise for instance, over the existence of",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      396.32,
      526.15,
      409.36
    ],
    "text": "a jurisdictional fact or the truthfulness of a particular witness where justice requires the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      414.32,
      352.82,
      457.0
    ],
    "text": "cross-examination be ordered. [emphasis added] This proposition was considered in the following cases,",
    "fonts": [
      "Century",
      "CenturySchoolbook",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      486.46,
      486.77,
      499.5
    ],
    "text": "In the case of Thajudeen Vs. Sri Lanka Tea Board and Another (1981) 2 SLR 471",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      506.26,
      411.74,
      519.3
    ],
    "text": "Ranasinghe J (as he was then) with Seneviratne J agreeing held:",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.38,
      534.1,
      526.13,
      547.14
    ],
    "text": "That the remedy by way of an application for a Writ is not a proper substitute for a",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
