      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      573.82,
      526.49,
      586.86
    ],
    "text": "truth, it is necessary that the questions should be canvassed in a suit where the parties",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      593.62,
      526.19,
      606.66
    ],
    "text": "would have ample opportunity examining their witnesses and the Court would be better",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      613.42,
      526.21,
      626.46
    ],
    "text": "able to judge which version is correct, has been laid down in the Indian cases of Ghosh v.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      633.22,
      526.46,
      646.26
    ],
    "text": "Damodar Valley Corporation, Porraju v. General Manager B. N. Rly4 (at page 474). The",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      653.17,
      253.8,
      666.21
    ],
    "text": "Court of Appeal further held that,",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      71.67,
      681.37,
      526.1,
      694.41
    ],
    "text": "Where the major facts are in dispute and the legal result of the facts is subject to",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
